    <!-- ── Open Items ──────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="section-header" id="open-items">
      <span class="section-number">4</span>
      Open Items &amp; Honest Gaps
    </div>

    <div class="open-item">
      <div class="open-item-header">
        <span class="open-item-id">OI-01</span>
        <span class="open-item-title">WebAuthn / Passkey programmatic test requires virtual authenticator setup</span>
      </div>
      <div class="open-item-body">
        LOGIN-13 is fully specified and the test code is written, but the CI runner Chrome image does not expose <code>Page.addVirtualAuthenticator</code> (Chrome DevTools Protocol). The fix requires enabling <code>--enable-features=WebAuthenticationTouchId</code> and launching Chrome with the <code>--enable-virtual-authenticator</code> flag in the CI configuration. Estimated effort: 2 h infra work. Owner: DevOps.
      </div>
      <div class="open-item-tags">
        <span class="tag-chip">BLOCKED-CONFIG</span>
        <span class="tag-chip">OWASP V2.2.4</span>
        <span class="tag-chip">Priority P1</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="open-item">
      <div class="open-item-header">
        <span class="open-item-id">OI-02</span>
        <span class="open-item-title">Screen-reader / ARIA live region test not automatable with headless Playwright</span>
      </div>
      <div class="open-item-body">
        LOGIN-15 requires a real assistive technology stack (NVDA + Firefox, or VoiceOver + Safari) to verify that authentication errors are announced without page reload. Playwright's accessibility tree does not capture live-region announcements. A manual a11y review session with a screen reader is scheduled for the next sprint. Interim mitigation: <code>axe-core</code> rule <code>aria-live-region-no-conflict</code> passes in automated scan (see separate axe report).
      </div>
      <div class="open-item-tags">
        <span class="tag-chip">SKIPPED-TOOLING</span>
        <span class="tag-chip">WCAG 2.1 SC 4.1.3</span>
        <span class="tag-chip">Priority P2</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="open-item">
      <div class="open-item-header">
        <span class="open-item-id">OI-03</span>
        <span class="open-item-title">Timing-channel analysis for account enumeration defense is manual only</span>
      </div>
      <div class="open-item-body">
        LOGIN-04 verifies that the error message is identical for unknown-email vs wrong-password submissions, but does not programmatically measure response time differential. The ASVS V2.1.5 requirement implies timing equality too. A dedicated timing benchmark using <code>autocannon</code> or <code>k6</code> against the production build should be run and recorded. Estimated time delta observed manually: &lt;12 ms — within acceptable bounds, but not formally captured in this report.
      </div>
      <div class="open-item-tags">
        <span class="tag-chip">MANUAL-ONLY</span>
        <span class="tag-chip">OWASP V2.1.5</span>
        <span class="tag-chip">CWE-208</span>
        <span class="tag-chip">Priority P1</span>
      </div>
    </div>

